				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ENC = 2 + \frac{9}{{F_{2} }} + \frac{1}{{F_{3} }} + \frac{5}{{F_{4} }} + \frac{3}{{F_{6} }}$$\end{document}ENC=2+9F2+1F3+5F4+3F6where Fk (k = 2, 3, 4 or 6) is the average of the Fk values for k-fold degenerate amino acids. The F value is the probability of two randomly chosen codons being identical for a particular amino acid.

